### Test Analytics SLA Compliance Endpoint
### Prerequisites: You need a valid JWT token from a government user (officer/admin/super_admin)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJlNDY5NjlmYS0zM2JiLTRhMzUtOTQ0Zi1lNmQ5NTdiZDJmYjciLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJuaXAiOiIxOTgwMDEwMTIwMDUwMTEwMDEiLCJhZ2VuY3lJZCI6IjAwMDAwMDAwLTAwMDAtMDAwMC0wMDAwLTAwMDAwMDAwMDAwMSIsImlhdCI6MTc3NjkxNzExNywiZXhwIjoxNzc2OTE4MDE3fQ.y2zPMk85xaqo0S4j4BW3acMJsFjWk1yfv56Si4NM4E8

### Test 1: Get SLA compliance metrics for 30 days (default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/sla?period=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 2: Get SLA compliance metrics for 90 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/sla?period=90
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 3: Get SLA compliance metrics for 365 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/sla?period=365
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 4: Test without authentication (should fail with 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/sla?period=30

### Test 5: Test with invalid period (should use default 30)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/sla?period=invalid
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 6: Test without period parameter (should use default 30)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/sla
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response Format:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "onTime": 45,
#     "breached": 12
#   }
# }

### SLA Targets by Priority:
# - P1 (urgent): 2 days
# - P2 (high): 7 days  
# - P3 (medium): 14 days
# - P4 (low): 30 days

### Notes:
# - Only includes completed reports (status: completed, verified_complete, closed)
# - Calculates days to completion: (completed_at - created_at) / 86400
# - Role-based filtering applies (officer sees only assigned, admin sees agency, super_admin sees all)
# - Results are cached for 5 minutes with key pattern: analytics:sla:{agencyId}:{period}